The police have arrested two brothers and a friend for the murder of a 56-year-old man. The suspects and the victim were drinking at a tavern in Mageva village outside Giyani in Limpopo, when the eldest suspect started accusing the victim of sleeping with his girlfriend.Police spokesperson Colonel Robert Netshiunda said the 56-year-old allegedly slapped the suspect with an open hand and a scuffle ensued. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>"The suspect allegedly stabbed the victim twice in the chest and once on the spinal cord."The other suspect hit the victim with a stone at the back of the head, while the third suspect was allegedly kicking the victim during the ordea," said NetshiundaHe said the victim was rushed to Nkhensani Hospital where he was certified dead on arrival. The suspects wanted to play hide and seek with the police but were arrested on Thursday night during Operation Thatha Zonke.The suspects will appear before the Giyani Magistrate’s Court on Monday, facing charges of murder.